reviewText: I was really disapponted.  Even though the movie was made over 20 years ago it showed great promise being that the book was written by Michener.  The story left you hanging--wondering what happened.  The plot itself was very choppy and unclear what happended between the chacters.  I am sorry I started the movie - now I will have to read the book to find out what happened.

Dynasty is a beautiful story of the settlers and how they worked hard. It moves fast through the years while they build their empire.
If you love Stacy Keach you will love this Triangle love.
The movie was good, I bought it because Harrison Ford was in it.  The ending just seems to leave you hanging.  It was more like they ran out of filming time and just tacked it onto the movie.
The dvd was as advertised. I would order from this company again.

Bought this because Amy Irving was in it and I believed she was one of the stars since her picture was on the cover but she was only in the movie for less than 2 minutes if I knew that I wouldn't have gotten it.
Ended way too soon!  Just stops . . .
it was ok and on time
Seemed like the first eoisode of a mini-series that never happened.

It was a pretty choppy mini-series but it added to my James Michener collection.
It was ok, I bought it because Harrison Ford is in it but he wasn't in it for more then probably 10 minutes.
As always, James Michener has woven a terrific story of deception, greed and jealousy in where?  OHIO?  How can that be!  Follow the trail thru 35 years of a family empire!
